322zp|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Esping-Andersen|first=G\u00f8sta|year=1991|title=The Three Worlds of Welfare Capitalism|location=Princeton, New Jersey|publisher=Princeton University Press|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=F\u00e9dorovski|first=Vladimir|year=2007|chapter=Situations VII|title=Le Fant\u00f4me de Staline|trans-title=The Ghost of Stalin|language=French|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Fitzpatrick|first=Tony|year=2003|title=After the New Social Democracy: Social Welfare for the Twenty-First Century|publisher=Manchester University Press|isbn=9780719064777|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last1=Fog|first1=Mogens|last2=Kragh|first2=Jens|last3=Larsen|first3=Aksel|last4=Moltke|first4=Kai|last5=Petersen|first5=Gert|year=1977|title=Folkesocialisme|language=Danish|publisher=SP Forl|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Foley|first=Michael|year=1994|title=Ideas that Shape Politics|publisher=Manchester University Press|page=23|isbn=978-0-7190-3825-9|quote=The virtual demise of communism [as represented by the Soviet Union and other communist states] has opened up the way for democratic socialism or social democracy as the major alternative to ''laissez-faire'', free market policies.|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Franklin|first=Robert Michael|year=1990|title=Liberating Visions: Human Fulfillment and Social Justice in African-American Thought|publisher=Fortress Press|isbn=9780800623920|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last1=Freeden|first1=Michael|last2=Sargent|first2=Lyman Tower|last3=Stears|first3=Marc|year=2013|title=The Oxford Handbook of Political Ideologies|location=Oxford|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=9780199585977|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Fryer|first=Peter|year=1957|chapter=The Second Soviet Intervention|title=Hungarian Tragedy|location=London|publisher=D. Dobson|ASIN=B0007J7674|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Fuchs|first=Christian|year=2017|title=Social Media: A Critical Introduction|edition=2nd|publisher=SAGE Publications|isbn=9781473987494|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite bo